X:1
T:Scotland the Brave
T:Pipe-band setting
C:Trad. Scottish (melody, late 19th c. or earlier; first widely
C:circulated through pipe-band repertoire by the early 20th century)
S:Public domain (US) — melody only. The Cliff Hanley lyrics (1951)
S:are NOT included; those remain in copyright.
N:Beginner pipe-band setting in A mixolydian for the 9-note Great
N:Highland chanter. AABA form (32 bars at L:1/8). NO RESTS — the
N:bag stores air, so the chanter never stops sounding. Phrasing is
N:articulated entirely through grace-note clusters: doublings on the
N:long notes, throw on D when D follows a lower pitch.
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=90
K:Amix
H:Standard 9-note GHP chanter range (G4-A5).
H:Arrangement: Heifer Zephyr / Tony Koop, 2026 (MIT, sheet-music repo).
H:Doubling pattern used throughout: {GdG} on low notes, {gag} on high A,
H:{ge} on E, {gf} on F#. These are written as ABC grace clusters in
H:braces; engravers will render them as small notes; MIDI will skip
H:them (grace notes don't sound on most pipe soundfonts anyway).
% --- A part (8 bars, repeat) ---
|: {GdG}A2 c2 e2 c2 | {gag}a2 f2 e2 c2 | {GdG}A2 c2 e2 c2 | {GeG}d2 c2 {GdG}A2 G2 |
   {GdG}A2 c2 e2 c2 | {gag}a2 f2 e2 c2 | f2 e2 c2 {GdG}A2 | {GBG}A8 :|
% --- B part (8 bars, repeat) — higher contour, sits on a' ---
|: {ge}e2 {gag}a4 a2 | {gf}f2 e2 c2 e2 | {ge}e2 {gag}a4 a2 | {gf}f2 e2 c4 |
   {ge}e2 {gag}a4 a2 | {gf}f2 e2 c2 e2 | f2 g2 a2 f2 | {GBG}A8 :|
